Timeline to proficiency

Month 1 — Solidify the Core
You finish tightening the fundamentals you already know:
    Clean Express architecture
    Controllers/services separation
    Error handling patterns
    Environment configs
    SQL fluency (joins, indexes, constraints)
    Using an ORM (Prisma or Drizzle)
    Building 2–3 clean CRUD modules
Outcome: You stop “figuring things out” and start flowing.




Month 2 — Authentication + Real API Features
This is where you level up fast.
    JWT + refresh tokens
    Sessions vs tokens
    Role-based access
    File uploads
    Pagination, filtering, sorting
    Redis caching
    Rate limiting
    Logging + monitoring
Outcome: You can build a production-style API with multiple modules.




Month 3 — Testing + Deployment
This is where you become dangerous.
    Unit tests (Jest)
    Integration tests
    Mocking DB calls
    Docker basics
    Deploying to Render/Railway/Azure
    CI/CD with GitHub Actions
    Linux basics (SSH, firewalls, PM2)
Outcome: You can deploy and maintain your own backend.




Month 4 — Architecture + Scaling
Now you start thinking like an engineer.
    MVC, service layers, repository patterns
    Caching strategies
    Message queues (BullMQ)
    Background jobs
    Microservices vs monoliths
    Performance tuning
    Security hardening
Outcome: You understand why systems are built the way they are.




Month 5–6 — Portfolio + Mastery
You build 2–3 real backend projects:
    Auth service
    Inventory system
    Hospital management API
    E‑commerce backend
    Logging dashboard
    Task manager with roles
You document everything.
You deploy everything.
You test everything.
Outcome: You’re employable, confident, and fully proficient.